Do regions respond in the same way to different stimulations?

#Number of samples per stimulation: #GFM: unstim 38, LPS 35, IFNy 23, R848 17, TNFa 23, ATP 4, DEX 10, IL4 8 #SVZ: unstim 29, LPS 29, IFNy 24, R848 24, TNFa 24, ATP 1 #GTS: unstim 30, LPS 25, IFNy 12 #THA: unstim 22, LPS 22, IFNy 9 #CC: unstim 15, LPS 16, IFNy 10

LPS

GFM x SVZ

#16108 genes

setwd("~/Documents/MiGASti/Databases")
DEG_LPS_GFM1 <- read.table("DEG_LPS_GFM.txt")
DEG_LPS_SVZ1 <- read.table("DEG_LPS_SVZ.txt")
DEG_LPS_GFM <- subset(DEG_LPS_GFM1, log2FoldChange > 1 | log2FoldChange < -1)
DEG_LPS_SVZ <- subset(DEG_LPS_SVZ1, log2FoldChange > 1 | log2FoldChange < -1)
DEG_genes_LPS_GFM_SVZ = merge(DEG_LPS_GFM, DEG_LPS_SVZ, by ="symbol")

GFM <- DEG_genes_LPS_GFM_SVZ[,4]
SVZ <- DEG_genes_LPS_GFM_SVZ[,11]
df = data.frame(GFM, SVZ)
p <- ggplot(df, aes(x=GFM, y=SVZ) ) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se=FALSE, color="black", formula = y ~ x) +
  geom_bin2d(bins = 100) +
  scale_fill_continuous(type = "viridis") +
  geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept = 0, linetype = 3) +
  theme_bw()
p + stat_cor(method = "spearman")
